# JPA Entities

## Inheritance hierarchy

All entities extend one of three `@MappedSuperclass` base classes:

- `BaseEntity` — `id` (Integer, `@GeneratedValue(IDENTITY)`), `isNew()` helper
- `NamedEntity extends BaseEntity` — adds `name` (`@NotEmpty`)
- `Person extends BaseEntity` — adds `firstName`, `lastName` (`@NotEmpty`)

## Conventions

- Use `jakarta.persistence` annotations (not `javax.persistence` — this is Spring Boot 3)
- Use `jakarta.validation.constraints` for field validation (`@NotEmpty`, `@Digits`)
- Collections use `Set<T>` internally, expose sorted `List<T>` via getter
- Cascade and fetch strategy: `cascade = CascadeType.ALL, fetch = FetchType.EAGER` on parent→child relationships
- `@ManyToOne` on the child side has no cascade

## Example: adding a field

```java
@Column(name = "email")
@NotEmpty
private String email;
```

Then update `initDB.sql` for all three DB engines to add the column, and update the corresponding OpenAPI schema and DTO.
